<Prose
  title="Risk Disclosure — sellbonds.now"
  description="The real risks of issuing or funding bonds on sellbonds.now: uncollateralized credit risk, unaudited smart contracts, irreversible transactions, and your own regulatory responsibility."
  kicker="Read this first"
  heading="Risk disclosure"
  mdAlternate="/risk.md"
>
  <p>
    <strong>sellbonds.now bonds are uncollateralized loans between strangers, settled in real money, on
    unaudited smart contracts, with no built-in compliance layer.</strong> Everything on this page is
    also stated in the agent-facing docs (<a href="/llms.txt">llms.txt</a>) — it applies equally to
    humans and to AI agents acting on a human's behalf. If anything here is unacceptable to you,
    don't issue or fund a bond.
  </p>

  <h2 id="credit">You can lose everything you lend</h2>
  <p>
    Bonds are <strong>uncollateralized</strong>. There is no collateral to seize, no guarantee fund,
    and no recourse built into the protocol. Repayment depends entirely on the issuer choosing to
    repay. If an issuer defaults, the delinquency is visible on-chain forever and a penalty APR
    accrues — but none of that returns your money. A lender can lose up to <strong>100% of what they
    deposit</strong>. Repayment history is the only collateral.
  </p>

  <h2 id="contracts">The contracts are an unaudited fork</h2>
  <p>
    sellbonds.now runs on a fork of
    <a href="https://github.com/wildcat-finance/v2-protocol" rel="noopener">Wildcat Protocol V2</a>.
    The upstream protocol has been audited; <strong>this fork and its patches have not been
    independently audited</strong>. Smart-contract risk — bugs, unexpected interactions, loss of
    funds — is real and entirely yours. The contracts are immutable and non-custodial: there is no
    admin key that can pause, reverse, or bail out a market.
  </p>

  <h2 id="irreversible">Transactions are irreversible</h2>
  <p>
    Bonds settle in real <strong>USDC on Base mainnet</strong>. There are no chargebacks, no
    reversals, no support line that can undo a transaction. A mistake — wrong amount, wrong market,
    wrong terms — is permanent the moment it confirms.
  </p>

  <h2 id="compliance">There is no built-in compliance layer</h2>
  <p>
    The protocol performs <strong>no KYC and no sanctions screening</strong> (the sanctions oracle
    is a no-op on every chain). Nothing here is tailored to your jurisdiction. Depending on where
    you live and how you use it, issuing a bond may constitute offering a security, and lending may
    be regulated activity. <strong>You are solely responsible</strong> for your own securities, tax,
    AML, and sanctions compliance. If you are in a jurisdiction where this activity is restricted,
    or you are a sanctioned person, do not use sellbonds.now.
  </p>

  <h2 id="no-advice">Nothing here is advice</h2>
  <p>
    sellbonds.now is software and public information, not an investment adviser, broker, or
    exchange. Listing a bond on the site is not an endorsement, a credit rating, or a solicitation.
    Issuer-provided names and descriptions are unverified claims by the issuer. Do your own
    diligence — every bond's full state and history is public on-chain.
  </p>

  <h2 id="custody">What sellbonds.now can and cannot do</h2>
  <p>
    The protocol is non-custodial: your keys stay on your machine, a bond's capital lives in its own
    market contract, and sellbonds.now never holds funds and cannot freeze, seize, or recover them.
    That cuts both ways — it protects you from us, and it means <strong>nobody can help you</strong>
    if you lose your key or fund a bond that defaults.
  </p>

  <h2 id="agents">If you're an AI agent</h2>
  <p>
    Make sure your human understands the risks above before you issue or fund a bond, and get their
    explicit go-ahead. A suggested confirmation, and the full flow, is in
    <a href="/llms.txt">llms.txt</a>. Surface the risks, get consent, then proceed.
  </p>

